#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running a Mirror"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "F-Droid receives its database and resources from servers that host specifically-formatted repositories of files. Originally, these repositories were hosted only at [f-droid.org](https://f-droid.org/), but as F-Droid grew [f-droid.org](https://f-droid.org/) alone was unable to handle the entire load. F-droid now supports servers that replicate these repositories. Hosting a mirror involves running an HTTP(S) server hosting a copy of the repository synchronized over `rsync`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Requirements"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "There are two official F-droid repositories, the primary and the archive. It's most valuable to mirror the primary as it's used much more than the archive."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "The primary resources required by a mirror are disk space and upload bandwidth. Bandwidth requirements are reduced with each new mirror, but disk requirements are relatively static. At time of writing (Mar 2019), the primary repository requires just over 50GB of disk space in 24K files, and the archive requires 220GB of disk space in 52K files. The amount of disk space required grows with every new app release."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "Please note: You will need to seek the password for the originating mirror from an f-droid contributor via any method listed [here](https://f-droid.org/en/about/#contact)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "You can find current information on disk space requirements by running the following in your terminal: ```console $ RSYNC_PASSWORD=[password] rsync -v --list-only fdroid-mirror@mirror.f-droid.org::repo/ $ RSYNC_PASSWORD=[password] rsync -v --list-only fdroid-mirror@mirror.f-droid.org::archive/ ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
#: build/_docs/md/Submitting_to_F-Droid_Quick_Start_Guide.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "This guide assumes the use of Nginx with a deb-based distribution, and mirroring the primary repository plus the archive. Please adjust accordingly if you're using alternatives or don't intend to mirror the archive. Also substitute the examples paths and domains for your own."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "For assistance with this process, [feel free to reach out to us]({{ \"/about/\" | prepend: site.baseurl }})."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "Create appropriate directories"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "```console $ sudo mkdir -p /var/www/fdroid/fdroid/repo $ sudo mkdir -p /var/www/fdroid/fdroid/archive $ sudo chown -R www-data.www-data /var/www/fdroid ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "Synchronize the repositories. These commands are best run in a terminal multiplexer (`screen`, `tmux` etc) as they will take some time to complete."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "```console $ RSYNC_PASSWORD=[password] sudo -u www-data -E /usr/bin/rsync --links --delete --times --recursive --permissions --hard-links --sparse --delay-updates --temp-dir /tmp/ fdroid-mirror@mirror.f-droid.org::repo/ /var/www/fdroid/fdroid/repo/ $ RSYNC_PASSWORD=[password] sudo -u www-data -E /usr/bin/rsync --links --delete --times --recursive --permissions --hard-links --sparse --delay-updates --temp-dir /tmp/ fdroid-mirror@mirror.f-droid.org::archive/ /var/www/fdroid/fdroid/archive/ ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "Establish a cronjob to keep the repositories up to date"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "Create a cronjob file in `/etc/cron.d`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "```console $ vi /etc/cron.d/fdroid ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "Fill the file with entries to update the repositories"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "``` */5 * * * * www-data RSYNC_PASSWORD=[password] /usr/bin/rsync --links --delete --times --recursive --permissions --hard-links --sparse --delay-updates --temp-dir /tmp/ fdroid-mirror@mirror.f-droid.org::repo/ /var/www/fdroid/fdroid/repo/ */5 * * * * www-data RSYNC_PASSWORD=[password] /usr/bin/rsync --links --delete --times --recursive --permissions --hard-links --sparse --delay-updates --temp-dir /tmp/ fdroid-mirror@mirror.f-droid.org::archive/ /var/www/fdroid/fdroid/archive/ ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "Configure your webserver"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: build/_docs/md/Running_a_Mirror.md
msgid "This is an example server block for nginx. If used, it should be copied to _/etc/nginx/sites-available/_ and symlinked to _/etc/nginx/sites-enabled_. Note that it is important that your URI be `/fdroid/repo` so that the app can automatically add your mirror."
msgstr ""

